<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3150447" xml-lang="en-US" level="1" l10n="CHG" oldref="1"><link href="text/scalc/01/05100000.xhp" name="Styles and Formatting">Styles and Formatting</link></paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3147434" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="2">Use the Styles and Formatting window to assign styles to objects and text sections. You can update Styles, modify existing Styles or create new Styles.</paragraph>
</section>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3149665" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="30">The Styles and Formatting <link href="text/shared/00/00000005.xhp#andocken" name="dockable window">dockable window</link> can remain open while editing the document.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_id3154321" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="E" localize="false"><link href="text/shared/00/00040500.xhp#gestalter"><embedvar href="text/scalc/00/00000004.xhp#wie"/></link></paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3150012" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="U" oldref="36">How to apply a cell style:</paragraph>
<list type="ordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3159155" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="37">Select the cell or cell range.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3145749" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="38">Double-click the style in the Styles and Formatting window.</paragraph>
</listitem>
</list>
