<paragraph role="heading" id="hd_id3148870" xml-lang="en-US" level="3" l10n="U" oldref="13">How to apply a new style with the paint can:</paragraph>
<list type="ordered">
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3145078" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="CHG" oldref="27">Select the desired style from the Styles and Formatting window.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3159098" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="28">Click the <emph>Fill Format Mode</emph> icon.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3148609" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="15">Click a cell to format it, or drag your mouse over a certain range to format the whole range. Repeat this action for other cells and ranges.</paragraph>
</listitem>
<listitem>
<paragraph role="listitem" id="par_id3149438" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="U" oldref="29">Click the <emph>Fill Format Mode</emph> again to exit this mode.</paragraph>
</listitem>
</list>
